{"id":76757,"title":"Accurate assessment patient weigh.","abstract":"Measuring patient weight is considered a routine assessment that is frequently delegated to unregistered staff. Yet patient weight is a fundamental part of nutrition assessment and may be used to calculate drug dosages and assess fluid balance. It is vital that staff carrying out this measurement are trained and have access to appropriate equipment that is regularly calibrated.","date":"2014-06-13","categories":"Nutritional and Metabolic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24923006","annotations":[{"name":"Weight","weight":0.273712,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weight"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.18053,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Drug","weight":0.174777,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug"},{"name":"Nutrition","weight":0.127891,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nutrition"},{"name":"Fluid","weight":0.125356,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluid"},{"name":"Measurement","weight":0.0391252,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Measurement"},{"name":"Calibration","weight":0.0391252,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calibration"},{"name":"Fluid balance","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluid_balance"},{"name":"Evaluation","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evaluation"},{"name":"Balance (ability)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Balance_(ability)"}]}
